Author: Strob#3417
Content: But about the fund spliting, I don't understand what it is, is there any explanation about this process anywhere?

Author: Mylo#8306
Content:
https://blog.komodoplatform.com/delayed-proof-of-work-explained-9a74250dbb86

do a search for 10000 in that.

Author: Mylo#8306
Content: the tl;dr; version is iguana does a multi-sig (ms) tx with XX number of signers, and the template ms tx uses 10k sataoshi as the amount.

Author: Mylo#8306
Content: if everyone uses the 10k ms tx template, it saves a whole round of negotiating UTXO sizes for the tx.   so by pre-splitting, and agreeing to the template of 10k sataoshi....basically "heaps easier"

Author: jorian#4555
Content: if you get elected, you'll soon learn that wallet / utxo management is an art

Author: jorian#4555
Content: every notarization uses one 10,000 sats utxo

Author: jorian#4555
Content: so when you did a bunch, youll need to do a splitfund again

Author: jorian#4555
Content: you can do a zillion of them initially, but that only slows down your node a lot, so the trick is to keep the wallet 'as light as possible'
